The wildest part hasn‚Äôt been learning the platform --it‚Äôs the trolls. The amount of people hiding behind an icon or fake name just to throw shade is INSANE.

And that‚Äôs what kills me is I run two fully transparent portfolios here. Growth portfolio is up 410% since inception, small-cap portfolio is up 291%. 15‚Äì20 names in each, all visible, all validated by a third party. I‚Äôve put it all out there for anyone to see.

I‚Äôve always tried to be transparent about what I own and how it‚Äôs performing. That‚Äôs why the animosity blows my mind sometimes -- because if you‚Äôve been part of this community, you‚Äôve seen me put it all out there.

Of course I‚Äôve had slip-ups. When you‚Äôre live-streaming at 6 AM or making calls that are too forward-looking for most to digest, you‚Äôre bound to miss the mark on delivery sometimes. But that‚Äôs the point of this game -- same info, different takes. That‚Äôs what makes markets the best game of all time.

I‚Äôve got thick skin -- college ball wired me that way -- but man, the personal vendettas some of these people carry? Wild.

End of rant. Just be kind to people. Life‚Äôs way too short.
